{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1267,"text":"My name is Dan Cohen\nand I am an academic, as he said."},{"time":4500,"text":"And what that means is that I argue."},{"time":7600,"text":"It's an important part of my life."},{"time":9267,"text":"And I like to argue."},{"time":10733,"text":"And I'm not just an academic,\nI'm a philosopher,"},{"time":14133,"text":"so I like to think that I'm actually\npretty good at arguing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17100,"text":"But I also like to think\na lot about arguing."},{"time":20367,"text":"And in thinking about arguing,\nI've come across some puzzles."},{"time":23867,"text":"And one of the puzzles is that,"},{"time":25800,"text":"as I've been thinking\nabout arguing over the years --"},{"time":28367,"text":"and it's been decades now --"},{"time":29800,"text":"I've gotten better at arguing."},{"time":31500,"text":"But the more that I argue\nand the better I get at arguing,"},{"time":35033,"text":"the more that I lose."},{"time":36967,"text":"And that's a puzzle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38233,"text":"And the other puzzle\nis that I'm actually okay with that."},{"time":41500,"text":"Why is it that I'm okay with losing"},{"time":43367,"text":"and why is it that I think good arguers\nare actually better at losing?"},{"time":46833,"text":"Well, there are some other puzzles."},{"time":48867,"text":"One is: why do we argue?"},{"time":50767,"text":"Who benefits from arguments?"},{"time":52433,"text":"When I think about arguments,\nI'm talking about --"},{"time":54800,"text":"let's call them academic arguments\nor cognitive arguments --"},{"time":57667,"text":"where something cognitive is at stake:"},{"time":59533,"text":"Is this proposition true?\nIs this theory a good theory?"},{"time":62300,"text":"Is this a viable interpretation\nof the data or the text? And so on."},{"time":66800,"text":"I'm not interested really in arguments\nabout whose turn it is to do the dishes"},{"time":70800,"text":"or who has to take out the garbage."},{"time":72500,"text":"Yeah, we have those arguments, too."},{"time":74833,"text":"I tend to win those arguments,\nbecause I know the tricks."},{"time":77600,"text":"But those aren't the important arguments."},{"time":79600,"text":"I'm interested in academic arguments,"},{"time":81400,"text":"and here are the things that puzzle me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84667,"text":"First, what do good arguers win\nwhen they win an argument?"},{"time":87767,"text":"What do I win if I convince you"},{"time":90267,"text":"that utilitarianism isn't really\nthe right framework"},{"time":92720,"text":"for thinking about ethical theories?"},{"time":94500,"text":"What do we win when we win an argument?"},{"time":96400,"text":"Even before that,"},{"time":97767,"text":"what does it matter to me"},{"time":99033,"text":"whether you have this idea\nthat Kant's theory works"},{"time":102000,"text":"or Mill is the right ethicist to follow?"},{"time":105200,"text":"It's no skin off my back"},{"time":106600,"text":"whether you think functionalism\nis a viable theory of mind."},{"time":110300,"text":"So why do we even try to argue?"},{"time":112367,"text":"Why do we try to convince other people"},{"time":114233,"text":"to believe things\nthey don't want to believe,"},{"time":116433,"text":"and is that even a nice thing to do?"},{"time":118233,"text":"Is that a nice way to treat\nanother human being,"},{"time":120500,"text":"try and make them think something\nthey don't want to think?"},{"time":123500,"text":"Well, my answer is going to make reference\nto three models for arguments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128199,"text":"The first model -- let's call it\nthe dialectical model --"},{"time":130967,"text":"is we think of arguments as war;\nyou know what that's like --"},{"time":133900,"text":"a lot of screaming and shouting\nand winning and losing."},{"time":136633,"text":"That's not a very helpful\nmodel for arguing,"},{"time":138800,"text":"but it's a pretty common\nand entrenched model for arguing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141567,"text":"But there's a second model for arguing:\narguments as proofs."},{"time":144833,"text":"Think of a mathematician's argument."},{"time":146933,"text":"Here's my argument.\nDoes it work? Is it any good?"},{"time":149733,"text":"Are the premises warranted?\nAre the inferences valid?"},{"time":154233,"text":"Does the conclusion follow\nfrom the premises?"},{"time":156800,"text":"No opposition, no adversariality --"},{"time":159233,"text":"not necessarily any arguing\nin the adversarial sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164933,"text":"But there's a third model to keep in mind"},{"time":166933,"text":"that I think is going to be very helpful,"},{"time":168933,"text":"and that is arguments as performances,\narguments in front of an audience."},{"time":173967,"text":"We can think of a politician\ntrying to present a position,"},{"time":176933,"text":"trying to convince\nthe audience of something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179100,"text":"But there's another twist on this model\nthat I really think is important;"},{"time":182600,"text":"namely, that when we argue\nbefore an audience,"},{"time":186633,"text":"sometimes the audience has\na more participatory role in the argument;"},{"time":190733,"text":"that is, arguments are also\n[performances] in front of juries,"},{"time":195267,"text":"who make a judgment and decide the case."},{"time":198067,"text":"Let's call this the rhetorical model,"},{"time":199900,"text":"where you have to tailor your argument\nto the audience at hand."},{"time":203633,"text":"You know, presenting a sound, well-argued,"},{"time":206300,"text":"tight argument in English\nbefore a francophone audience"},{"time":209700,"text":"just isn't going to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211800,"text":"So we have these models --\nargument as war, argument as proof"},{"time":215467,"text":"and argument as performance."},{"time":218167,"text":"Of those three, the argument as war\nis the dominant one."},{"time":222467,"text":"It dominates how we talk about arguments,"},{"time":225100,"text":"it dominates how we think about arguments,"},{"time":227167,"text":"and because of that,\nit shapes how we argue,"},{"time":230167,"text":"our actual conduct in arguments."},{"time":231967,"text":"Now, when we talk about arguments,"},{"time":233667,"text":"we talk in a very militaristic language."},{"time":235667,"text":"We want strong arguments,\narguments that have a lot of punch,"},{"time":238933,"text":"arguments that are right on target."},{"time":240633,"text":"We want to have our defenses up\nand our strategies all in order."},{"time":243833,"text":"We want killer arguments."},{"time":246433,"text":"That's the kind of argument we want."},{"time":249200,"text":"It is the dominant way\nof thinking about arguments."},{"time":251633,"text":"When I'm talking about arguments,"},{"time":253267,"text":"that's probably what you thought of,\nthe adversarial model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256445,"text":"But the war metaphor,"},{"time":258966,"text":"the war paradigm or model\nfor thinking about arguments,"},{"time":261733,"text":"has, I think, deforming effects\non how we argue."},{"time":265100,"text":"First, it elevates tactics over substance."},{"time":268967,"text":"You can take a class\nin logic, argumentation."},{"time":271133,"text":"You learn all about the subterfuges"},{"time":272867,"text":"that people use to try and win\narguments -- the false steps."},{"time":275767,"text":"It magnifies the us-versus\nthem aspect of it."},{"time":278967,"text":"It makes it adversarial; it's polarizing."},{"time":282400,"text":"And the only foreseeable outcomes\nare triumph -- glorious triumph --"},{"time":288233,"text":"or abject, ignominious defeat."},{"time":291333,"text":"I think those are deforming effects,"},{"time":293100,"text":"and worst of all, it seems\nto prevent things like negotiation"},{"time":296967,"text":"or deliberation or compromise\nor collaboration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302233,"text":"Think about that one -- have you\never entered an argument thinking,"},{"time":305424,"text":"\"Let's see if we can hash something out,\nrather than fight it out."},{"time":308833,"text":"What can we work out together?\""},{"time":310767,"text":"I think the argument-as-war metaphor"},{"time":313163,"text":"inhibits those other kinds\nof resolutions to argumentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317600,"text":"And finally -- this is really\nthe worst thing --"},{"time":320067,"text":"arguments don't seem to get us\nanywhere; they're dead ends."},{"time":322900,"text":"They are like roundabouts or traffic jams\nor gridlock in conversation."},{"time":328600,"text":"We don't get anywhere."},{"time":330433,"text":"And one more thing."},{"time":331733,"text":"And as an educator, this is the one\nthat really bothers me:"},{"time":334667,"text":"If argument is war,"},{"time":336867,"text":"then there's an implicit equation\nof learning with losing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341900,"text":"And let me explain what I mean."},{"time":344067,"text":"Suppose you and I have an argument."},{"time":346633,"text":"You believe a proposition, P, and I don't."},{"time":350500,"text":"And I say, \"Well, why do you believe P?\""},{"time":352438,"text":"And you give me your reasons."},{"time":353867,"text":"And I object and say,\n\"Well, what about ...?\""},{"time":356267,"text":"And you answer my objection."},{"time":357800,"text":"And I have a question:\n\"Well, what do you mean?"},{"time":360233,"text":"How does it apply over here?\""},{"time":362133,"text":"And you answer my question."},{"time":363800,"text":"Now, suppose at the end of the day,"},{"time":365533,"text":"I've objected, I've questioned,"},{"time":367667,"text":"I've raised all sorts of counter\ncounter-considerations"},{"time":370287,"text":"and in every case you've responded\nto my satisfaction."},{"time":373900,"text":"And so at the end of the day, I say,"},{"time":376567,"text":"\"You know what? I guess you're right: P.\""},{"time":380500,"text":"So, I have a new belief."},{"time":382867,"text":"And it's not just any belief;"},{"time":384304,"text":"it's well-articulated, examined --\nit's a battle-tested belief."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391800,"text":"Great cognitive gain."},{"time":392984,"text":"OK, who won that argument?"},{"time":395600,"text":"Well, the war metaphor\nseems to force us into saying you won,"},{"time":399567,"text":"even though I'm the only one\nwho made any cognitive gain."},{"time":402300,"text":"What did you gain, cognitively,\nfrom convincing me?"},{"time":405967,"text":"Sure, you got some pleasure out of it,\nmaybe your ego stroked,"},{"time":408967,"text":"maybe you get some professional status"},{"time":410967,"text":"in the field --\n\"This guy's a good arguer.\""},{"time":413567,"text":"But just from a cognitive point of view,"},{"time":416567,"text":"who was the winner?"},{"time":417867,"text":"The war metaphor forces us into thinking\nthat you're the winner and I lost,"},{"time":422700,"text":"even though I gained."},{"time":424767,"text":"And there's something wrong\nwith that picture."},{"time":427067,"text":"And that's the picture\nI really want to change if we can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429800,"text":"So, how can we find ways"},{"time":433173,"text":"to make arguments\nyield something positive?"},{"time":437633,"text":"What we need is new\nexit strategies for arguments."},{"time":441367,"text":"But we're not going to have\nnew exit strategies for arguments"},{"time":444267,"text":"until we have new entry\napproaches to arguments."},{"time":447600,"text":"We need to think\nof new kinds of arguments."},{"time":451267,"text":"In order to do that, well --"},{"time":453867,"text":"I don't know how to do that."},{"time":456100,"text":"That's the bad news."},{"time":457467,"text":"The argument-as-war metaphor\nis just ... it's a monster."},{"time":460500,"text":"It's just taken up habitation in our mind,"},{"time":462919,"text":"and there's no magic bullet\nthat's going to kill it."},{"time":465390,"text":"There's no magic wand\nthat's going to make it disappear."},{"time":468049,"text":"I don't have an answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469333,"text":"But I have some suggestions."},{"time":470700,"text":"Here's my suggestion:"},{"time":473700,"text":"If we want to think\nof new kinds of arguments,"},{"time":475908,"text":"what we need to do\nis think of new kinds of arguers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479900,"text":"So try this:"},{"time":482767,"text":"Think of all the roles\nthat people play in arguments."},{"time":487233,"text":"There's the proponent and the opponent"},{"time":490233,"text":"in an adversarial, dialectical argument."},{"time":492433,"text":"There's the audience\nin rhetorical arguments."},{"time":494600,"text":"There's the reasoner\nin arguments as proofs."},{"time":498767,"text":"All these different roles."},{"time":500100,"text":"Now, can you imagine an argument\nin which you are the arguer,"},{"time":503967,"text":"but you're also in the audience,\nwatching yourself argue?"},{"time":507967,"text":"Can you imagine yourself\nwatching yourself argue,"},{"time":511033,"text":"losing the argument, and yet still,\nat the end of the argument, saying,"},{"time":515533,"text":"\"Wow, that was a good argument!\""},{"time":519133,"text":"Can you do that?"},{"time":520500,"text":"I think you can, and I think\nif you can imagine that kind of argument,"},{"time":523832,"text":"where the loser says to the winner\nand the audience and the jury can say,"},{"time":527633,"text":"\"Yeah, that was a good argument,\""},{"time":529600,"text":"then you have imagined a good argument."},{"time":531482,"text":"And more than that,"},{"time":532667,"text":"I think you've imagined a good arguer,"},{"time":534667,"text":"an arguer that's worthy of the kind\nof arguer you should try to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539567,"text":"Now, I lose a lot of arguments."},{"time":542367,"text":"It takes practice to become a good arguer,"},{"time":544800,"text":"in the sense of being able to benefit\nfrom losing, but fortunately,"},{"time":547980,"text":"I've had many, many colleagues\nwho have been willing to step up"},{"time":550967,"text":"and provide that practice for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552700,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553899,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}